{
  "name": "Sanguine Sphere",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Chinoike.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You form a large 10-foot sphere of water in front of you and spit fresh blood into a sphere, turning it completely red. You then move the sphere to a point within range and cause it to explode into shards of water.</p><p>Each creature of your choice within 20 feet of the sphere when it explodes must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, creatures take 6d6 cold damage and gain 2 ranks of bleeding, or half the ranks of bleeding as ranks of Lacerated if they are currently Lacerated. If an affected creature already has ranks of bleeding or is Lacerated, on a failed save, you can alternatively choose to give them the Weakened condition for the duration of their bleeding and/or lacerated condition.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above C-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3, the damage by 1d6, and the ranks of bleeding by +1</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
